                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus target="#1 #9">1ra-vb, 9ra-rb</locus>
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>                       
                        <date>Hand a: of recent period (20th century?)</date>                        
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="2ra" to="8vb">2ra-8vb</locus>
                        <locus from="104a" to="152vb">104a-152vb</locus>
                        <seg type="script">Hand b: mediocre. </seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        The scribe is Ḫāyla Krǝstos
                        (s. the supplication formula, <locus target="#104vb">104vb</locus>); the
                        name of ʿAmda Śǝllāse in the supplication formula on <locus target="#132ra">132ra</locus> has been added in a different hand.
                        <date>Hand b: 18th
                           century. </date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; name of the protagonist; names of the
                           donors and scribes; groups of lines (alternating with black lines) in the
                           incipit page of Text I; a few lines of the incipits of Texts II-VI;
                           incipits of sections/miracles of Texts I and II; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="153ra" to="155vb">153ra-155vb</locus>
                        <seg type="script">Hand c: fine,
                           careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>Hand c: of recent period (20th century?)</date>                        
                     </handNote>
                     
                     
